  dialogue:
    waystones:
    - key: sunfield-meadow
      text: Walk gently. The meadow fed them, too, and they are under it.
    - key: bramble-hedgerows
      text: The stone does not grow back. Take it like you mean it.
    - key: old-growth-wood
      text: These roots drink deeper than you will ever dig. Let them.
    - key: silverrun-river
      text: 
    provisioner:
    - id: prov-01
      trigger: first-visit
      line: Sell me nothing you would weep to lose. I do not give refunds, and the
        land does not either.
    - id: prov-02
      trigger: after-migration
      line: The last warden asked fewer questions. Hm. Perhaps that was the trouble.
    migrationVignette:
    - The camp folds. The land exhales.
    - What you gave, it keeps.
    fossilCards:
    - key: antler-crown
      text: A crown of bone for a king of no kingdom. The meadow remembers being
        afraid, and will not say of what.
    - key: sunken-jaw
      text: 
    - key: those-who-planted
      text: 
